  "title": "Mergers & Acquisitions",
  "description": "<p>Reporting to the Head of M&amp;A and working with other senior team members, you will support M&amp;A deals in terms of origination and execution as follows:</p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Performing financial valuation analysis such as relative valuation (including comparable valuation, precedent transactions, takeover premia). M&amp;A valuation analysis (including accretion/dilution, synergy value) and fundamental valuation (including DCF modeling, LBO modeling)</li>\n  <li>Preparing market and industry analysis</li>\n  <li>Identifying and evaluating potential targets / sellers / investors / buyers</li>\n  <li>Preparation and organization of documents for origination: organization of public information booklets for internal and external use, pitch books to clients, teasers, engagement letters, internal committee approval documents</li>\n  <li>Identifying merits of the M&amp;A transaction when evaluating deals, taking into account strategic business and financial aspects of the entities concerned and the industry(ies) which they operate in</li>\n  <li>Participating in live M&amp;A process: coordinating due diligence with legal, accounting and tax consultants, advising on optimal transaction structures, advising clients on negotiation strategy, drafting of correspondences on behalf of clients, and reviewing transaction documents</li>\n  <li>Cooperating and working closely with the M&amp;A teams in overseas offices</li>\n</ul>\n<p><strong>Requirements:</strong></p>\n<ul>\n  <li>Good Bachelor's degree in Accountancy, Business, Law, Science or Arts</li>\n  <li>Minimum 3-4 years' of experience in Investment Banking/Corporate Finance/M&amp;A/Audit</li>\n  <li>Must be fluent in English (both spoken and written). Fluency in Japanese language will be an added advantage to handle Japanese clients/counterpart and relevant pitchbooks.</li>\n</ul>",
